parameters:
Mage Relm: Clea-san is gradually starting to resemble...
Agonia-san, isn't she?

Priestess Sophia: Mmm, huff, pufaa! With this, negotiations
will go perfectly.

Sister Eleo: You said that the alcohol decreased... Is that
true?

Thief Nora: Ahaha... I don't have anything to say about
that...
Sister Eleo: I will give you bread later.
Thief Nora: Yes, I always drink!

Priestess Sophia: It's sad to be sold for just one piece of
bread...

Are you going to the second floor where the noble Pido from
the Senate is?
Clea (Let's prepare first and then go.)
Clea: Please hide yourself, Prince Rex.

Prince Rex: We've come this far, there's no way we can
just--
Priestess Sophia: Please let me help as well.

Priestess Sophia: The opponent is Pido, who behaves like a
king in the campus. This whole situation might be a trap to
lure Prince Rex out.

Priestess Sophia: First, let us go and assess the situation
ourselves.

Prince Rex: It's pointless to say anything with that
expression. However, if things start to get strange
upstairs, I'll go too.

Clea: Thank you very much. Your overwhelming presence
completely dominated that man. It was truly impressive.

Prince Rex: Thanks to you, I was able to face myself.
Without those words, I wouldn't have been able to do it.

Priestess Sophia: I-I'm fine... I was completely overwhelmed
by Prince Rex's presence.

Prince Rex: I have also made up my mind. Let's return to
Dromos and inform everyone.
Priestess Sophia: Yes, I will accompany you.

Priestess Sophia (This is what I wished for... but what is
this feeling?)

Priestess Sophia (The person I loved, who would change
because of Prince Rex... It's as if they're becoming a
completely different person.)
Priestess Sophia (...I can't shake off this uneasiness)

Novice Maid: Yes! I'll do anything for Master Pido!
............Hey, you! Where did you come from?
Veteran Maid: Welcome to Lord Pido's mansion.

Novice Guard: 'Pid-sama is quite sharp. You better be
careful too.'
Veteran Maid: Welcome to Lord Pido's mansion.
